Commentary.Commentary: That is all from this game. The action continues in the Hundred as Trent Rockets will take on Manchester Originals. The Women's will be in action first. Join us on the 19th of this month at 7.30 pm IST (2 pm GMT) and earlier for the build up. Cheers.

Sam Curran wins the PLAYER OF THE MATCH AWARD. He says it's a big win for them. Shares the staff, players and coaches have been incredible and it's nice to turn up to work. Tells Jordan Cox is in good form, he is timing well and today took pressure off him. Ends by saying the games are coming thick and fast and hopes they keep on winning.

Southern Brave have now lost three successive matches. They have tumbled down in this tournament after winning their first two games. Defending a score has been an issue for them as they have lost all three games in the second half. Today, the batters need to take the blame. They were punished against some quality bowling. Rashid Khan and Sam Curran run riot against Southern Brave as the former picked three wickets in five balls while Curran stepped up in the fag end of the innings. While defending, they had the bowlers but none made an impact to get the team into the game.

A crushing win by Oval Invincibles and they make it four wins in five matches to stay on top of the table. Statement win by them. A side which knows how to play under difficult conditions. A score of 133 was not going to be easy to chase. Oval Invincibles took their time, lost a couple of wickets (the openers) in the process but Sam Curran and Jordan Cox joined hands, were watchful initially but paced their innings brilliantly to put in a 101-run stand and bury this game. Both scored respective fifties and got the team over the line.
TWO AND THAT WILL IT! A length ball, outside off, Curran punches it to deep cover for a couple of runs. Sam Curran ends with a fifty to his name. Oval Invincibles win by 7 wickets.
